         <abstract id="aspace_a545cf26c44a8c7dab3c95a9e3cd2479">Letters by Rossetti to various parties, including Sir Frederic Burton and Frederic James Shields, along with one letter from Charles Augustus Howell to Rossetti. One manuscript by Rossetti: "At Wellington's Funeral. 18th November 1852," an autograph receipt, and a deck of playing cards painted by Rossetti at the age of 12.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n79117985" source="naf">
               <part>Rossetti, Dante Gabriel, 1828-1882</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_9929f626281316bba78aa9cab3263593">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition note</head>
         <p>Ongoing collection of documents acquired by gift and purchase from various sources. Type of accession (gift or purchase) and date of acquisition is noted in the box-and-folder list. For further information, consult the appropriate curator.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <userestrict id="aspace_22b1501528bbefc3690e80cf1e0a9ac0">
         <head>Ownership  Copyright</head>
         <p>The Dante Gabriel Rossetti Collection is the physical property of the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University. Literary rights, including copyright, belong to the authors or their legal heirs and assigns. For further information, consult the appropriate curator.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_6f9ceca282f7b821b90620d98c0ff611">
         <head>Cite As</head>
         <p>Dante Gabriel Rossetti Collection. General Collection, Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_2894ff5964b285122b82f1e5448bc994">
         <head>Information about Access</head>
         <p>This collection is open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <processinfo id="aspace_8c3772335c0c880f171b7445d6e38f2f">
         <head>Processing Notes</head>
         <p>This finding aid was produced from previously existing cards in the Manuscripts Catalog, or from another inventory. All pertinent bibliographical information has been retained. If the collection also contains unlisted or unsorted material, it has been noted in the box-and-folder list. This finding aid will be updated periodically to account for new materials that may be added to the collection. The date of the most recent update is noted on the title page. For information on material that may have been added since the last update, please consult the Public Service Desk.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_4cb9ff21fe0ca6938ac985685f5669fe">
         <head>Description of the Papers</head>
         <p>This finding aid encompasses accessions of single manuscripts and small groups of manuscripts and other papers, by or pertaining to Dante Gabriel Rossetti, which the library has chosen to group and list as an artificial collection. Materials incorporated into the collection prior to June 1997 have been organized into three series. <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="ref10">Series I, <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                  <part>Correspondence</part>
               </title> 
            </ref>, principally contains items written by Rossetti, with one letter written to Rossetti by Charles Augustus Howell. The single item in <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="ref44">Series II, <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                  <part>Writings</part>
               </title> 
            </ref>, is a manuscript poem. The <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="ref47">
               <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                  <part>Other Materials</part>
               </title> in Series III</ref> consist of an autograph receipt and a set of playing cards painted by Rossetti at the age of 12.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
